<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-03-20T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-03-20T02:00:00-05:00" n="764" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d764">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/1105: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jarvis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-20T15:00:00+08:00">March 20,
                                    1939—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received March 20—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>65. Japanese controlled vernacular press reported March 15 joint
                            promulgation by Japanese Navy and Army Special Service Sections of
                            regulations controlling navigation on Yangtze between Hukow, Kiangsi,
                            and Yochow, Hupeh, on Han up to Hanchuan and on Poyang <pb facs="0785" n="781" xml:id="pg_781"/> Lake. Navy prohibited all vessels,
                            including even sampans, unless provided with a permit issued by Navy and
                            Army Special Service Sections. Violation of provision requiring permit
                            punishable by confiscation of vessel and cargo. Garrison units
                            responsible for inspection of vessels. Permit application procedure
                            established for Japanese and Chinese but not other nationals.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Chungking, Peiping, Shanghai.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Jarvis</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>